Sampling from a population
========================================================

Throwing a six face die

Create the die
```{r}
die <-seq(from=1, to=6, by=1)
```
Throw the die
```{r}
sample(x=die, size=1, replace=T)
```

Sampling from a population
========================================================

Throw the 1000 times and keep the results
```{r}
die_results <- sample(x=die,
                      size=1000,
                      replace=T)
```


Sampling from a population
========================================================

Plot the results
```{r, eval=F}
hist(die_results,
     breaks=seq(from=0.5,
                to=6.5,
                by=1))
```
***
```{r,echo=F}
hist(die_results,
     breaks=seq(from=0.5,
                to=6.5,
                by=1))
```


